Quote:  The public campaign will focus on seven projects in its first six months: a game show for Maori Television; a radio drama serial for native speakers; a bilingual "radio-sode" (or short episodes) aimed at young people; an interactive website; a resource kit for new parents; phrase booklets; and a language event to promote Matariki, or Maori New Year. ... "That we now have funding to undertake specific projects - such as the quiz show for Maori Television and the funky new 'radio-sode' - is a sign of the positive commitment that the Government has made in its role to support the Maori language. ... Radio "Brown Street", a series of 30-second bilingual "radio-sodes" - or short episodes - produced by youth music station Mai FM in association with Te Taura Whiri.
